  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air, then preheat the grill to high</p><p>Boil a kettle and chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cook for 12-15 min or until fork tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2102.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2102.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2102.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2102.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2102.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong>, then peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, your <strong>garam masala</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>paprika</strong> and small dollop of your <strong>natural yoghurt</strong> in a large bowl (save the rest for later!)</p><p>Season with <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and add the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> – this is your <strong>tikka marinade</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
